# Run Code Style Enforcer After Code Changes

When modifying Python code in this project, you MUST run the code-style-enforcer agent.

## Triggers

Run code-style-enforcer when:
- Creating new Python files
- Modifying existing Python files (classes, methods, functions)
- Adding or changing type hints
- Adding or changing docstrings

## Files Requiring Style Enforcement

| Modified File Type | Action |
|--------------------|--------|
| `*.py` in framework root | Run code-style-enforcer |
| `*.py` in `event_examples/` | Run code-style-enforcer |
| `*.py` in `test_bots/` | Run code-style-enforcer |

## When to Skip

You may skip code-style-enforcer for:
- Documentation-only changes (README.md, IMPLEMENTATION.md, BOTS.md)
- Configuration file changes
- Rule/agent definition changes (.cursor/rules/, .cursor/agents/)

## Checklist

After Python code changes:
- [ ] Run code-style-enforcer agent on modified files
- [ ] Verify all style violations are fixed
- [ ] Confirm mypy passes (if type hints were modified)
